models <- list()
set.seed(123)
for (i in 1:164) {
  models[[i]] <- randomForest(x = X_train, y = Y_train[, i],
                              mtry=23, ntree=51)
}

plot(models[[1]])

print(models[[1]])
## 
## Call:
##  randomForest(x = X_train, y = Y_train[, i], ntree = 51, mtry = 23) 
##                Type of random forest: regression
##                      Number of trees: 51
## No. of variables tried at each split: 23
## 
##           Mean of squared residuals: 164.2479
##                     % Var explained: 34.44
predictions <- matrix(NA, nrow = nrow(X_test), ncol = length(models))
for (i in 1:length(models)) {
  model <- models[[i]]
  predictions[, i] <- predict(model, newdata = X_test)
}

predictions_model1 <- predictions[, 1]
rmse_model1 <- sqrt(mean((predictions_model1 - Y_test[, 1])^2))
cat("RMSE for model 1:", rmse_model1, "\n")
## RMSE for model 1: 14.26497
predicted_values <- predictions[, 1]
actual_values <- Y_test[, 1]

plot_data <- data.frame(
  Observed = as.numeric(actual_values),
  Predicted = as.numeric(predicted_values),
  Std_Error = apply(predictions, 1, sd)  
)
ggplot(plot_data, aes(x = Observed, y = Predicted)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = Predicted - Std_Error, ymax = Predicted + Std_Error), width = 0.2) +
  geom_abline(intercept = 0, slope = 1, color = "red") +
  labs(x = "Observed", y = "Predicted", title = paste("Observed vs PredictedY1 (Model 1)")) +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(legend.position = "none")

models12 <- list()
set.seed(123)
for (i in 1:164) {
  models12[[i]] <- randomForest(x = X_train, y = Y_train12[, i],
                                mtry=18, ntree=81)
}

plot(models12[[150]])

print(models12[[150]])
## 
## Call:
##  randomForest(x = X_train, y = Y_train12[, i], ntree = 81, mtry = 18) 
##                Type of random forest: regression
##                      Number of trees: 81
## No. of variables tried at each split: 18
## 
##           Mean of squared residuals: 5.534327
##                     % Var explained: 21.65
predictions12 <- matrix(NA, nrow = nrow(X_test), ncol = length(models12))
for (i in 1:length(models12)) {
  model12 <- models12[[i]]
  predictions12[, i] <- predict(model12, newdata = X_test)
}

predictions_model12 <- predictions12[, 1]
rmse_model12 <- sqrt(mean((predictions_model12 - Y_test12[, 1])^2))
cat("RMSE for model 1:", rmse_model12, "\n")
## RMSE for model 1: 2.779319
predicted_values12 <- predictions12[, 1]
actual_values12 <- Y_test12[, 1]

plot_data12 <- data.frame(
  Observed = as.numeric(actual_values12),
  Predicted = as.numeric(predicted_values12),
  Std_Error = apply(predictions12, 1, sd)  
)
ggplot(plot_data12, aes(x = Observed, y = Predicted)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = Predicted - Std_Error, ymax = Predicted + Std_Error), width = 0.2, alpha = 0.25) +
  geom_abline(intercept = 0, slope = 1, color = "red") +
  labs(x = "Observed", y = "Predicted", title = paste("Observed vs PredictedY12 (Model 1)")) +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(legend.position = "none")
